{"id":731,"date":"2022-04-18T16:19:00","date_gmt":"2022-04-18T13:19:00","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/?p=731"},"modified":"2022-03-23T19:46:58","modified_gmt":"2022-03-23T17:46:58","slug":"online-credit-card-payments-explained","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/online-credit-card-payments-explained\/","title":{"rendered":"Credit Card Payments Explained"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>Used well, banking as a service platform provides a safe and reliable way to <a href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/how-multiple-payment-gateways-help-merchants-sell\/#:~:text=Anyone%20looking%20to%20expand%20their%20business%20to%20a%20global%20scale%20should%20consider%20whether%20their%20current%20payment%20provider%20can%20handle%20such%20a%20shift\">make online Credit Card Payments<\/a> and pay for goods and services. Most modern consumers use credit cards to help them achieve this goal.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Though convenient, credit cards can prove problematic if you run up a bill or choose to make minimum payments. You need to find a way to balance your usage and monthly debt repayments.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>A failure to do so may cause you to accumulate a large debt forcing collectors to come after you. Understanding what credit cards are, how a credit card payment works, and the behind-the-scenes processes involved in a credit card transaction can enable you to manage your debt.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div id=\"ez-toc-container\" class=\"ez-toc-v2_0_45 counter-hierarchy ez-toc-counter ez-toc-grey ez-toc-container-direction\">\n<div class=\"ez-toc-title-container\">\n<p class=\"ez-toc-title\">Table of Contents<\/p>\n<span class=\"ez-toc-title-toggle\"><a href=\"#\" class=\"ez-toc-pull-right ez-toc-btn ez-toc-btn-xs ez-toc-btn-default ez-toc-toggle\" area-label=\"ez-toc-toggle-icon-1\"><label for=\"item-673d664b813ed\" aria-label=\"Table of Content\"><span style=\"display: flex;align-items: center;width: 35px;height: 30px;justify-content: center;direction:ltr;\"